univention-grub (7.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bump version for UCS 3.2, update copyright years for 2013
  * Add a new UCR variable grub/rootdelay, which configures the time the initrd waits
    until a mount of the root device is attempted. This prevents boot failures for 
    some hardware setups, which initialises the root device slowly. By default five
    seconds are being waited, this can be disabled by setting the variable to 0.
    Bug #31071

 -- Moritz Mühlenhoff <muehlenhoff@univention.de>  Fri, 12 Jul 2013 12:39:07 +0200

